                </list>
                
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>Coat of Arms</figDesc>
                </figure>
                
                <hi rend="caps">WE'RE MOVING TO FLORIDA!</hi>
                
                <p>This will be the last school year in St. Louis. In June, we move to our new home in the Coconut Grove section of Miami, Florida.</p>
                
                <p>As usual during the summer, we will conduct the school program at
                    <address>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">CAMP IRONWOOD</hi></addrLine>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">HARRISON, MAINE</hi></addrLine>
                    </address>
                </p>
                
                <p>We will start the school year in September 1959 at our new address
                    <address>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">SEBAGO SCHOOL</hi></addrLine>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">3525 CRYSTAL VIEW COURT</hi></addrLine>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">MIAMI, FLORIDA</hi></addrLine>
                    </address>
                </p>
                
                <p>While in St. Louis, it has been our policy not to accept local students. The local child has too many <hi rend="underline">outside</hi> interests and object relationships to feel the immediate need to turn to us for his emotional satisfactions. Also, there is the constant problem of interference from old friends, relatives and his immediate family.</p>
                
                <p>In Miami, we plan to continue the same policy of not accepting local children. However, this will mean that for the first time, we will be able to welcome children from the St. Louis area.</p>
                
                <p><hi rend="caps">AT THE PRESENT TIME, WE CAN ACCEPT TWO NEW STUDENTS EIGHT YEARS OF AGE OR OLDER.</hi></p>
                
                <note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></note>
                
            </div1>
